## Common Patterns

### Components
- Most components are TypeScript (.tsx)
- Function components with hooks
- Uses Tailwind for styling

### Context API
- `DarkModeContext` provides dark mode state globally
- Used in components that need theme-aware rendering

### Routing
- React Router v6 with JSX route definition
- Consider using `useNavigate()` for programmatic navigation
- Link components for navigation

## Build Configuration
- Vite config uses `@vitejs/plugin-react` (Babel for fast refresh)
- TypeScript build before Vite bundling
- Autoprefixer and PostCSS preset-env for browser compatibility

## Notes for Contributors
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Use Context API for global state (dark mode is a good example)
- Maintain TypeScript strict mode
- Run `npm run lint` before committing
- Test dark mode functionality when making visual changes
